Reasoning: The paper deals with training generative models, specifically the variational autoencoder (VAE), which is a popular topic in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning. The paper proposes a new objective function and a new technique to address the problem of posterior collapse in VAEs, which is a common issue in generative models. This makes the paper relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and software engineering (cs.SD).
